summary: Can we have a reunion scene between Thor and Loki à la Sherlock, when John discovers Sherlock isn't dead. Some time after the...
body:
Can we have a reunion scene between Thor and Loki à la Sherlock, when John discovers Sherlock isn’t dead. Some time after the snap, Thor goes to a bar to get drunk and forget and complain about himself to the bartender, who is Loki with a beard and glasses (basically a very Tom Hiddleston look) and Loki, as the little bastard he is, just drags Thor down with every complaint:

Thor: I had one chance and I blew it. The head. Why didn’t I go for the head?

Loki: Clearly you didn’t have a…, em, good head on your shoulders.

Thor: Half of the universe died because of me.

Loki: Thank you.

Thor: My brother sacrificed for me. It was all for nothing.

Loki: Yeah, well, I guess I’d rather be dead for good than listen to all this nonsense.

Thor: You’re clearly not helping, aren’t you?

Loki: You’re clearly not seeing. Are you sure your new eye is working?

Thor: What are you -? *looks up, squints*… Loki?

Loki, dramatically taking off his glasses: Hello brother. Short version… Not dead.

Thor: I saw you die.

Loki: Well I did, but then I came back. Again.

Thor: How is that possible.

Loki: Long version, I -

Thor: *punches Loki*

summary:
“What do you mean no?”
All day he’d been fighting with himself. Hulk didn’t want to come out, pouting after Bruce had yelled at...
body:
“What do you mean no?”

All day he’d been fighting with himself. Hulk didn’t want to come out, pouting after Bruce had yelled at him. He was angry at him, tired of losing track of time, of not being in control. Hulk took it too personally and refused to show himself, let alone fight, since then. But this was serious. He needed his help. You were in trouble and only he could save you.

“Hulk, please. Y/n needs your help.”

“Y/n?” Hulk gasped.

“Yes! Yes y/n. All I need you to do is-” But, before he could finish, Hulk had already taken over, pushing the two of them off the ground, determined to destroy everything in his path until he could find you and get you to safety. With a little guiding from Bruce, he found his way to you.
